The default is black so I don't need to Cetaphil here.

18
00:01:27.030 --> 00:01:29.770
Cool let's move on to Jamaica.

19
00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:35.660
I've used the same background color trick here but I'll set it to black for the green and yellow parts

20
00:01:35.660 --> 00:01:36.380
of the flag.

21
00:01:36.410 --> 00:01:42.230
I could create a bunch of different polygon or patho elements but instead I'll just create two one for

22
00:01:42.230 --> 00:01:45.920
each green triangle to add the yellow part of the flag.

23
00:01:45.950 --> 00:01:52.520
I'll set a stroke and stroke width on the polygons since both polygons will have the same color styles.

24
00:01:52.520 --> 00:01:58.150
I'll create a group and set stroke stroke with infill attributes at the group level.

25
00:02:00.040 --> 00:02:04.240
Inside of my group I'll create a polygon for the top triangle.

26
00:02:04.240 --> 00:02:09.760
Note that if I put the corners of the triangle at the corners of the Viji the yellow stroke also applies

27
00:02:09.760 --> 00:02:10.700
to the top.

28
00:02:10.720 --> 00:02:12.700
I don't want to fix this.

29
00:02:12.730 --> 00:02:18.000
I'll back up the top corners so that they fall outside the bounds of the SPG.

30
00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:24.760
Now I can do something similar for the bottom triangle just with different y coordinates OK.

31
00:02:25.050 --> 00:02:26.720
Next for Macedonia.

32
00:02:26.760 --> 00:02:32.370
I'll set the background color to this red shade and then I'll create a group whose bill is this yellow

33
00:02:32.380 --> 00:02:36.230
color to get the rays coming out of the circle.

34
00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:45.580
I'll just make four polygons one for each diagonal one for the vertical raise and one for the horizontal

35
00:02:45.580 --> 00:02:46.210
ones.

36
00:02:47.130 --> 00:02:51.630
I had to play around a bit with these coordinates to get the flag looking right so don't worry if this

37
00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:52.430
takes a guess.

38
00:02:52.440 --> 00:03:00.900
Check next I'll place the circle in the middle of the flag and give it a read stroke so that the rays

39
00:03:01.060 --> 00:03:02.710
are separated from the circle.

40
00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:07.210
Onwards to the last flag.

41
00:03:07.330 --> 00:03:09.310
This one is definitely a little trick.

42
00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:17.310
First let me focus on the black bars to draw them I'll create a group and set stroke stroke with and

43
00:03:17.310 --> 00:03:18.590
transform attributes.

44
00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:24.590
Ungroup I'm transforming to the center of the SVGA because I'm going to create these lines vertically

45
00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:31.370
and then rotate them and I want to be sure I rotate about the center of the Viji not the origin which

46
00:03:31.370 --> 00:03:32.810
is in the upper left corner.

47
00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:36.250
So that I can practice with paths.

48
00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:38.880
Let me use patho elements for most of this.

49
00:03:38.990 --> 00:03:44.040
First I'll draw the three lines at the upper left in the six lines and the bottom right of the flag

50
00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:47.380
for the solid lines on the left.

51
