Move the cursor.

52
00:03:48.610 --> 00:03:50.470
Draw a vertical line down.

53
00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:51.420
Move over.

54
00:03:51.490 --> 00:03:53.060
Draw a vertical line up.

55
00:03:53.260 --> 00:03:56.490
Move over again and draw another vertical line down.

56
00:03:57.540 --> 00:04:03.540
Then move over to the other side of the SVGA take a similar approach but this time only to draw a short

57
00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:04.430
line down.

58
00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:05.910
Move the cursor down a bit.

59
00:04:05.940 --> 00:04:07.540
Try another short line down.

60
00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:10.210
Move the cursor over a bit and so on.

61
00:04:11.450 --> 00:04:14.360
So that I don't need to keep track of absolute coordinates.

62
00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:17.210
I'm using lower case letters for the bulk of this command.

63
00:04:18.850 --> 00:04:20.120
This looks pretty good.

64
00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:22.140
So now let me rotate it.

65
00:04:22.600 --> 00:04:23.830
Great.

66
00:04:23.830 --> 00:04:24.360
Next.

67
00:04:24.400 --> 00:04:27.640
Do something very similar for the second set of lines.

68
00:04:27.640 --> 00:04:31.340
